$interpreted:
Dagger: Huff... Puff...
Damnit! That Tica, no idea how, but she sure runs fast!
Dagger: I don't have time to waste fighting you folks!
Dagger: Judging by footprints, she should be running this way!
Sherlock: Sigh!
Ned: Sir Sherlock, is something bothering you?
Lisa: Ned, can you please hand me that vase over there?
Ned: This one?
Sherlock: SIGH!!!
Lisa: Yep, this is it. Thank you, Ned.

Lisa: Here you go~ This is the vase you ordered.
Your mother will definitely be happy when she received this Christmas gift.
Sherlock: SIGH!!!
Lisa: Father! What's your deal this time!?

Sherlock: Look at her; even that little girl remembers to buy her mom a present! You've completely forgotten about me ever since you got married.
You spend all your time caring only about Ned.

Sherlock: The previous, adorable little Lisa would never do something like that!
SIGHS~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Lisa: Well, blame yourself! It was father's idea to host this Christmas sale thing. We were so busy that I barely have time to prepare your present.
Lisa: Not only are you not helping out, but your constant sighs are also really noisy and annoying.
Sherlock: I don't care! Gimme back my adorable little Lisa!

Ned: Lisa, stop making him sweat.
After all, you did prepare a surprise for Sir Sherlock...
Tica: Wooaaaahh!? So many people here!!

Tica: The Christmas Girl is here!
Come~ presents for everybody!
Sherlock: My oh my, look at this girl; she traveled so far just to deliver presents. She is so much kinder than my own daughter, hmph!
Lisa: Father! One more temper tantrum from you and you'll be cooking your own dinner tonight...
Dagger: Damnit! One step behind, again!
Dagger: Excuse me. She handed out the wrong presents.
Sherlock: HEY! You stupid bear! Gimme back my present!

Lisa: Father!? Where are you going!
Come back! Father!!!
Ned: Lisa! Sir Sherlock!
Ned: Apologies, we are closing early today.
Ned: Lisa, wait for me!
Kittyeyes: Did you guys see a big bear?
